The paper discusses fast algorithms for finding the most likely configuration of large-scale DPPs, which are probabilistic models commonly used in machine learning tasks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques and algorithms, which could place it in the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses matrix determinants and log-determinants, which are commonly used in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT, and cs.SI, in that order.
